On Escalation Ticket # 00425972 the new comment has been added: Alexandra-Alina Pascalau:

Hi Emil,

Thank you for the link. The EscalationAttachmentFolder in the ADO task has a different link(../Data/00425874), that's why I wasn't able to see anything.

I noticed that the debug log file was not created in the correct path and that is why it is empty.
The correct path is 
           /var/log/epp/export_entities.log 
     

Please redo the test:


	 - 	Delete already created exports that have not finished:


--- CODE ---
                DELETE FROM export_entities WHERE export_status=0;
--- CODE ---

     2. Enable debugging for the export cron with the correct path:

--- CODE ---
              touch /tmp/export_entities.debug
              touch /var/log/epp/export_entities.log
              chmod 777 /var/log/epp/export_entities.log
--- CODE ---

      3. Run a onetime export of Users. 
          I noticed there are fewer users , so first test the users export and if the users export is working test the onetime computers export next.

      4. While you wait for the export,  run this mysql query a few times and provide screenshots:


--- CODE ---
              show full processlist;
--- CODE ---

       5. Provide the debug file /var/log/epp/export_entities.log


       6. Disable the debugging:

               rm /tmp/export_entities.debug

Ask the customer if it is possible that he filters and deletes some of the entities (computers, users) that he thinks are not needed. 
I see that there are some computers that do not have a user assigned or users that have not been assigned to any computer.

Regards,
Alina
